SUMMARY:Free Composting Basics Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Registration is required. Sign up below. \n\nFind out how to 
 compost at home and use compost in your garden or on your house plants. 
 Residents can see live demonstrations to build and maintain a backyard 
 compost pile and worm compost bin in our FREE workshops hosted by the 
 University of California Composting Education Program and the City’s Zero 
 Waste Program. \n\nTo see the full list of classes available throughout the 
 year\, visit link.ucanr.edu/composted. Mountain View residents can attend 
 any of the Santa Clara County workshops for free.
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Kyle Hval":MAILTO:kyle.hval@mountainview.gov
