BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260603T180000Z
DTEND:20260603T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260603T000000Z
SUMMARY:Your Ticket to the Best State Fair Crafts with Smithsonian Curator Mary Savig
DESCRIPTION:Registration is required. Click this link to attend the virtual 
 event.\n\nJoin us for a fascinating discussion with Smithsonian Curator 
 Mary Savig on the history and significance of craft at state fairs—from 
 blue-ribbon quilts to sculpted butter cows\, and so much more!\n\nA Dolly 
 Parton crop art portrait. Size-96 cowboy boots. A button quilt. State 
 Fairs: Growing American Craft features more than 100 photos of 
 extraordinary and unconventional crafts from state and tribal fairs\, 
 including needlework\, basketry\, jewelry\, ceramics\, crop art\, butter 
 sculpture\, and saddles. The catalog highlights personal stories and 
 regional and cultural traditions\, creating a vibrant portrait of American 
 life. Come one\, come all! State Fairs has a little something for 
 everyone.\n\nRegister now to hear about the fascinating (and often 
 surprising) world of American state fair crafts!\n\nNot able to attend 
 live? You can access the recording for this event and all Online Author 
 Series events on our website shortly after they conclude.\n\nAbout the 
 Author:\n\nMary Savig is The Fleur and Charles Bresler Curator-in-Charge of 
 the Smithsonian American Art Museum’s Renwick Gallery. She holds a PhD in 
 American Studies from the University of Maryland\, College Park.\n\n 
 \n\n\n\nThis event is generously sponsored by the Friends of the Mountain 
 View Library.
LOCATION:Online
ORGANIZER;CN="Kyle Hval":MAILTO:kyle.hval@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Author Talk
UID:LibCal-8800-16699302
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/16699302
END:VEVENT
