SUMMARY:STEAM Fridays
DESCRIPTION:\n\nGet ready to tinker\, build\, explore\, and create!\n\nJoin 
 us for STEAM Fridays\, a drop-in program full of hands-on activities that 
 spark curiosity and creativity. Whether you're a budding scientist\, an 
 imaginative engineer\, or an artistic innovator\, there’s something for 
 everyone to discover.\n\nEach week features a variety of self-directed 
 projects in Science\, Technology\, Engineering\, Art\, and Math\, perfect 
 for curious minds who love to experiment and play.\n\n\n\nSome projects 
 might get a little messy. Please dress appropriately.\n\n \n\n\n\nThis 
 event is generously sponsored by the Friends of the Mountain View Library.
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Renee Kitson":MAILTO:renee.kitson@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:
UID:LibCal-8800-16535153
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/16535153
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260613T180000Z
DTEND:20260613T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260613T000000Z
SUMMARY:Low-Water Lawn Alternatives
DESCRIPTION:Seating is limited. Registration is recommended. Walk-ins are 
 also welcome. \n\nAre you tired of mowing\, watering and fertilizing? Would 
 you like to use less water and create a landscape that is more sustainable? 
 Is your lawn dead but you don’t know what to do next? Come and hear 
 Master Gardener Martha Carpenter explain how to downsize or eliminate your 
 lawn and replace it with low water ornamentals\, grasses\, and ground 
 covers. Assessing your needs and evaluating your site will be discussed and 
 suggestions for hardy plants and grasses for our climate will be 
 given.\n\nInfrared assistive listening systems are available for use during 
 this event. Please see Library staff for assistance.\n\n
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Charles Mosner":MAILTO:charles.mosner@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Nature & Gardening
UID:LibCal-8800-14959846
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/14959846
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260615T220000Z
DTEND:20260615T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260615T000000Z
SUMMARY:Wildmind Science Learning
DESCRIPTION:Beautiful and fascinating wildlife live in the fields and 
 forests surrounding our cities and suburbs. Children will gain an insight 
 into the secret lives of these intelligent and ecologically important 
 animals. Our teachers will include a Grey Fox\, Kingsnake\, Red-Tailed 
 Hawk\, and Skunk!\n\n
LOCATION:Pioneer Park
ORGANIZER;CN="Alex Pantazes":MAILTO:alexandra.pantazes@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Just for Fun (Youth), Learn & Explore
