BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260623T180000Z
DTEND:20260623T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260623T000000Z
SUMMARY:Simple\, Sustainable\, and Powerfully Delicious Meals with Sana Javeri Kadri and Asha Loupy
DESCRIPTION:Registration is required. Click this link to attend the virtual 
 event.\n\nJoin us as we chat with Sana Javeri Kadri and Asha Loupy about 
 The Diaspora Spice Co. Cookbook\, which celebrates beautiful\, simple\, and 
 seasonal cooking with 85 recipes adapted from India and Sri Lanka’s best 
 family spice farms.\n\nDiaspora Spice Co. sources the most flavorful\, 
 fresh spices in the world from 150 regenerative farms across South 
 Asia—from elders\, indigenous communities\, young changemakers\, and 
 brilliant multi-generational farming families across India and Sri Lanka 
 who are leading the way in sustainable and climate change–resistant 
 agriculture. Filled with culinary storytelling\, The Diaspora Spice Co. 
 Cookbook highlights these farmers and their spices with profiles and 
 evocative photography\, plus 85 recipes for simple\, seasonal\, and 
 powerfully delicious meals.\n\nCEO and founder Sana Javeri Kadri and recipe 
 writer Asha Loupy realized that eating with the people who grow our spices 
 unveils a whole new dimension in our cooking. Adapted for a global pantry\, 
 these recipes share the warmth of true South Asian home cooking at its 
 truest and tastiest.\n\nSana and Asha also note which recipes are the most 
 beginner friendly\, freezer friendly\, good for a dinner party menu (like a 
 Diwali feast!)\, and which lend themselves to be pantry building blocks\, 
 all for a super easy-to-navigate cookbook.\n\nRegister now to learn more 
 about Diaspora Spice Co.\, the progressive spice company rooted in flavor 
 and equity. \n\nNot able to attend live? You can access the recording for 
 this event and all Online Author Series events on our website shortly after 
 they conclude.\n\nAbout the Authors:\n\nSana Javeri Kadri is the founder 
 and CEO of Diaspora Co.\, a farm-to-table spice company that puts equity\, 
 transparency\, and high-quality products at its forefront. Sana founded the 
 company in 2017 with just a turmeric blend\; now her company sources 30 
 single origin spices from across 150 farms across India and Sri Lanka. A 
 third-generation native of Mumbai\, she now lives in Oakland\, 
 California.\n\nAsha Loupy is a recipe developer and writer with more than a 
 decade of experience in the specialty food industry\, from cheese monger to 
 grocery buyer and e-commerce manager. She’s written for Bon Appétit\, 
 Food52\, Epicurious\, and more. She’s based in Oakland\, 
 California.\n\n\n\nThis event is generously sponsored by the Friends of the 
 Mountain View Library.
LOCATION:Online
ORGANIZER;CN="Kyle Hval":MAILTO:kyle.hval@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Author Talk, Just For Fun (Adult)
UID:LibCal-8800-16700208
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/16700208
END:VEVENT
