SUMMARY:Super Smash Bros Tournament
DESCRIPTION:Do you have what it takes to be a Super Smash Bros. Ultimate 
 champion? Test your skills against other players and compete in a series of 
 rounds to determine a victor. Please register so you can be added to the 
 tournament bracket. If you'd just like to watch\, no registration 
 necessary! Devices and controllers are provided\, but feel free to bring 
 your own. Please take care to label your controllers so they do not get 
 mixed up with library-provided controllers. \n\nAges 8 -12.  \n\nThere will 
 be a second tournament for teens\, ages 13-18\, in July.\n\nRuleset will be 
 time-based and length determined by number of tournament participants. 
 Items will be ON (medium frequency\, no Smash Ball) and FS meter ON (fill 
 up a gauge to reach Final Smash). Spirits will be OFF.\n\nAfter 
 registering\, please send your FIGHTER CHOICE and PLAYER NAME to 
 annika.koltermann@mountainview.gov before 3pm on June 22 to set up the 
 bracket. Please choose from the main fighter roster of 74\; no DLC 
 characters are available but all base characters are unlocked.
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Annika Koltermann":MAILTO:annika.koltermann@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Just for Fun (Youth)
