BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260627T210000Z
DTEND:20260627T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260627T000000Z
SUMMARY:Jazz in the Park: The Lunar Octet
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy an exciting afternoon of live music at Pioneer Park with 
 award-winning group The Lunar Octet\, known for its dynamic sound\, rich 
 arrangements\, and high-energy performances. With infectious rhythms and 
 powerful solos\, The Lunar Octet promises an unforgettable outdoor concert 
 experience.\n\nPlease bring your own chairs and blankets. \n\nThe Lunar 
 Octet plays original and eclectic music drawing on Cuban and Puerto Rican 
 salsa\, rock\, African high-life music\, and Brazilian sambas to forge a 
 new sound enriched by these traditions. The group's original compositions 
 involve rich arrangements and strong focus on soloists. The group's music 
 is exciting\, dynamic\, and powerful\, including fiery Latin grooves\, 
 driving funk rhythms\, swinging bop tunes\, and romantic ballads.\n\nTheir 
 newest CD\, “Convergence” (Summit Records) has gotten airplay on more 
 than 325 radio stations world-wide and has gotten rave reviews from the 
 worldwide jazz press. The award winning group’s hundreds of performances 
 include the Montreux-Detroit Jazz Festival\, the Michigan Jazz Festival\, 
 the Scarborough Jazz Festival\, the Columbus Jazz & Rib Fest\, the Flint 
 Jazz Festival\, the Thunder Bay Jazz Festival\, the Ann Arbor Blues and 
 Jazz Festival\, the Lancaster Festival\, the Ann Arbor Summer Festival\, 
 the Portola Vineyards Jazz Concert Series\, The Ark\, Rusty’s Jazz 
 Café\, the Blue Llama Jazz Club\, the Dirty Dog Jazz Club\, Shain Park\, 
 Cadillac Pavilion for the Arts\, The Ohio State University\, the University 
 of Michigan\, Denison University\, and more.\n\n\n\nThis event is 
 generously sponsored by the Friends of the Mountain View Library.
LOCATION:Pioneer Park
ORGANIZER;CN="Kyle Hval":MAILTO:kyle.hval@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Musical Performances
UID:LibCal-8800-16448227
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/16448227
END:VEVENT
