SUMMARY:Don't Squash that Bug! Recognizing Beneficial Insects in the Garden
DESCRIPTION:Seating is limited. Registration is recommended. Walk-ins are 
 also welcome. \n\nOur gardens are home to a host of insects that prey upon 
 or parasitize the insects that attack our plants. Master Gardener Candace 
 Simpson will help you learn how to recognize these “natural enemies\,” 
 distinguish them from common pest insects\, and encourage them to make your 
 garden their home. Other methods for managing common insect pests will also 
 be discussed.\n\nInfrared assistive listening systems are available for use 
 during this event. Please see Library staff for assistance.\n\n
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Charles Mosner":MAILTO:charles.mosner@mountainview.gov
