SUMMARY:San Francisco Dance Film Festival
DESCRIPTION:Seating is limited. Registration is recommended. Walk-ins are 
 also welcome. \n\nThis diverse program brings together standout short films 
 from the 2025 San Francisco Dance Film Festival\, offering a dynamic 
 snapshot of the creativity\, craft\, and global perspectives that defined 
 the year.\n\nSpanning playful surrealism\, intimate portraits\, and urgent 
 social inquiry\, the program moves from the mythic landscapes of French 
 Polynesia to the backstreets of Sevilla\, from hand-drawn animation 
 inspired by scientific innovation to raw explorations of family and 
 identity.\n\nHighlights include multiple SFDFF 2025 award winners\, 
 alongside bold experiments that pair dance with robotics\, poetry\, and 
 cultural ritual. Together\, these works showcase dance film as a powerful 
 storytelling medium-one that bridges tradition and technology\, personal 
 reflection and collective memory.\n\nRecommended for ages 16 \n\n 
 \n\n\n\nThis event is generously sponsored by the Friends of the Mountain 
 View Library.
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Charles Mosner":MAILTO:charles.mosner@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Arts & Crafts (Adult), Friends of the Library, Just For Fun (Adult)
