SUMMARY:Amplify: Unscripted--Building Confident Young Speakers
DESCRIPTION:An interactive summer workshop created to help young people 
 develop one of the most valuable life skills: the ability to think clearly 
 and speak confidently in front of others. Led by Meera Kalluraya\, a 
 nationally recognized speech and debate competitor with multiple state and 
 national awards in Impromptu and Informative Speaking\, the program teaches 
 practical communication skills that students can use in classrooms\, 
 interviews\, presentations\, leadership roles\, and everyday conversations. 
 The participants learn proven frameworks for organizing ideas quickly\, 
 managing nerves\, using effective vocal delivery and body language\, and 
 transforming prompts\, quotes\, or personal experiences into engaging 
 speeches. \n\nAges 11 \n\nThis event is part of Amplify: Teen Voices\, a 
 program for teens who want to share their interests and passions with an 
 audience.
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Alex Pantazes":MAILTO:alexandra.pantazes@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Amplify, Workshops
