DTEND:20260729T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260729T000000Z
SUMMARY:Make Protein Goals Easy (and Satisfying!) with Dietitian Rachael DeVaux
DESCRIPTION:Registration is required. Click this link to attend the virtual 
 event.\n\nJoin us for an energizing virtual conversation with Rachael 
 DeVaux\, New York Times bestselling author of Rachael’s Good Eats. Her 
 newest book\, The High Protein Plate\, shows how anyone at any stage of 
 life can easily incorporate protein into their diet. From Buffalo Chicken 
 Baked Tacos and Honey Blackberry Overnight Oats to Creamy Tomato Basil 
 Chicken Pasta\, these satisfying and simple meals are made for everyday 
 life.\n\nGetting enough protein is essential. It’s needed for health and 
 strength at every stage of life. The more protein you eat\, the more 
 satisfied\, energized\, and resilient you’ll feel. It builds muscle\, 
 fuels hormones\, and supports every organ.\n\nThe High Protein Plate 
 includes the following:\n\n- 100 high-protein\, craveable recipes for 
 packing protein from breakfast through dessert.\n\n- Straightforward 
 guidance on how much protein you really need—and why it matters.\n\n- 
 Macros for every recipe\, so you can easily track what’s best for 
 you.\n\n- Confidence to plan and prepare balanced\, purposeful meals.\n\n- 
 Meal prep tips to set you up for success all week long.\n\n- A 28-day plan 
 to help get you started and stay on track.\n\nWhether you’re focused on 
 building lean muscle\, balancing blood sugar\, boosting energy\, or just 
 feeding your family well you need protein. The High Protein Plate makes it 
 simple—and delicious to get enough every day.\n\nRegister today to learn 
 delicious ways you can incorporate protein into your meals!\n\nNot able to 
 attend live? You can access the recording for this event and all Online 
 Author Series events on our website shortly after they conclude.\n\nAbout 
 the Author: Rachael DeVaux is the author of the instant New York Times 
 bestseller Rachael’s Good Eats. A registered dietitian\, certified 
 personal trainer\, and entrepreneur\, she has built a loyal audience of 
 over a million people through her website and Instagram by sharing 
 practical\, science-backed guidance on food\, fitness\, and feeling good. 
 She lives in Seattle\, Washington\, with her husband and young son. Visit 
 RachaelsGoodEats.com to learn more.\n\n\n\nThis event is generously 
 sponsored by the Friends of the Mountain View Library.
LOCATION:Online
ORGANIZER;CN="Kyle Hval":MAILTO:kyle.hval@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Author Talk, Health & Wellness
UID:LibCal-8800-16953175
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/16953175
END:VEVENT
