SUMMARY:Teen Super Smash Bros. Tournament
DESCRIPTION:Do you have what it takes to be a Super Smash Bros. Ultimate 
 champion? Test your skills against other players and compete in a series of 
 rounds to determine a victor and win a prize. Please register so you can be 
 added to the tournament bracket. If you'd just like to watch\, no 
 registration necessary! Devices and controllers are provided\, but feel 
 free to bring your own. Please take care to label your controllers so they 
 do not get mixed up with library-provided controllers. \n\nAges 13-18 
 \n\nThere is another tournament for ages 8-12 on June 25th.\n\nRuleset will 
 be time-based and length determined by number of tournament participants. 
 Items will be ON (medium frequency\, no Smash Ball) and FS meter ON (fill 
 up a gauge to reach Final Smash). Spirits will be OFF.\n\nAfter 
 registering\, please send your FIGHTER CHOICE and PLAYER NAME to 
 annika.koltermann@mountainview.gov before 3pm on July 27 to set up the 
 bracket. Please choose from the main fighter roster of 74\; no DLC 
 characters are available but all base characters are unlocked.
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
