BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260827T180000Z
DTEND:20260827T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260827T000000Z
SUMMARY:High Altitudes and High Stakes: A Miss Marple Mystery with Lucy Foley
DESCRIPTION:Registration is required. Click this link to attend the virtual 
 event.\n\nJoin us for a thrilling conversation with acclaimed author Lucy 
 Foley as we delve into her brand-new Miss Marple mystery\, Murder at the 
 Grand Alpine Hotel. \n\nHigh in the Swiss Alps\, accessible only by a 
 single\, winding railway\, stands the luxurious Grand Alpine Hotel. With 
 glorious mountain views and exclusive access to powdery slopes\, it draws 
 guests from far and wide. \n\nThe notorious actress. \n\nThe high-flying 
 politician. \n\nThe society wife. \n\nThe reckless friend. \n\nThe shrewd 
 doctor. \n\nBut not everyone is here for a winter holiday. Beneath the 
 champagne and furs\, dark histories simmer\; old grudges emerge like cracks 
 in the ice. And someone is watching from the shadows. A polite\, unassuming 
 woman with an extraordinary mind: Miss Marple. When a body is found and a 
 blizzard cuts off all escape\, only Miss Marple can connect the clues 
 before the killer strikes again. Because it isn’t a question of who has a 
 motive\, but who’s next…\n\nNot able to attend live? You can access the 
 recording for this event and all Online Author Series events on our website 
 shortly after they conclude.\n\nAbout the Author: Lucy Foley is a No.1 
 Sunday Times\, Irish Times and New York Times bestselling author. More than 
 10 million copies of her books are in print worldwide\, and several are 
 currently being adapted for the screen. She is a Waterstones Thriller of 
 the Month author\, a three-time nominee at the British Book Awards\, and 
 The Guest List was a Reese’s Book Club selection and winner of the 
 Goodreads Choice Award for Mystery Thriller. As a life-long Agatha Christie 
 fan\, Lucy has drawn immeasurable inspiration from the Queen of Crime. She 
 was one of 12 writers to contribute to Marple\, a collection of short 
 stories featuring the beloved detective. And in Murder at the Grand Alpine 
 Hotel\, she was inspired to transport Miss Marple – her favorite Christie 
 creation – to the glamorous post-war setting of the Swiss Alps\, in a 
 mystery that feels gloriously escapist yet utterly relevant to our 
 times.\n\n\n\nThis event is generously sponsored by the Friends of the 
 Mountain View Library.
LOCATION:Online
ORGANIZER;CN="Kyle Hval":MAILTO:kyle.hval@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Author Talk
UID:LibCal-8800-16953208
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/16953208
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260829T210000Z
DTEND:20260829T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260829T000000Z
SUMMARY:How to Start Solo Traveling the World
DESCRIPTION:Registration is recommended. Seating is limited. Walk-ins are 
 also welcome.\n\nAre you 55-plus and craving a more adventurous and fun 
 life? Solo travel can change your life\, giving you fresh perspectives and 
 authentic joy. You can slow-travel the planet or stay in one location for a 
 month or more. In this presentation\, author\, photographer\, and 
 experienced solo traveler Mary Bartnikowski will share information and 
 photos from her travels\, offer tips on how to start solo traveling\, and 
 answer questions from the audience.\n\nWe'll cover:\n\n\n	How to change 
 your mindset to plan your own adventures and not wait for anyone\n	Exact 
 guidance on how to choose the best destinations\n	How to get the best 
 prices on accommodation and flights\n	How to plan a 3-month vacation or 
 sabbatical\n	Safety Plan for Solo Travelers\n	Join Mary Bartnikowski's Free 
 Age 50 to 100 Travel Newsletter\n\n\nAbout the Presenter: Mary Bartnikowski 
 is the founder of an award winning photography business who has lived in 
 Palo Alto for 40 years. Mary has hosted 11 one-woman exhibitions\, she is 
 the author of 6 books on solo traveling Amazon\, a leader of private 
 photography retreats in Italy and Mexico\, and she has traveled in 34 
 countries solo in the last 20 years. She has presented speaking events at 
 at Apple\, Intel\, Stanford\, University of Hawaii\, and San Mateo County 
 libraries. Mother of a cool son.\n\n\n\nThis event is generously sponsored 
 by the Friends of the Mountain View Library.
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Kyle Hval":MAILTO:kyle.hval@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Just For Fun (Adult)
UID:LibCal-8800-16870058
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/16870058
END:VEVENT
