BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20261015T013000Z
DTEND:20261015T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20261014T000000Z
SUMMARY:Ukulele Jam Sing and Play Along
DESCRIPTION:Registration is recommended. Seating is limited. Walk-ins are 
 also welcome. \n\nWould you like to learn some fun songs on the ukulele? 
 Beginners and ukulele enthusiasts are welcome to join us to sing and play 
 together. Ukulele instructor Chuck Monahan will teach participants how to 
 play basic chords on the ukulele and lead the group in an informal 
 performance of popular songs from the last 50 years. Bring your own uke\, 
 or use one of ours. \n\nAges 12 and up only.\n\n \n\n\n\nThis event is 
 generously sponsored by the Friends of the Mountain View Library.\n
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Ashley Lang":MAILTO:ashley.lang@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Just For Fun (Adult)
UID:LibCal-8800-17028028
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/17028028
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20261017T173000Z
DTEND:20261017T203000Z
DTSTAMP:20261017T000000Z
SUMMARY:Drop-in Bike Clinic
DESCRIPTION:Come join us every third Saturday of the month for the Drop-in 
 Bike Clinic!\n\n \n\nUse our tools to work on your bike. All ages 
 welcome.\nProfessional bike mechanic Ryan Murphy will be available for 
 advice and help with:\n\n\n	Changing a tire\n	Adjusting gears and 
 brakes\n	Identifying that mysterious noise\, and more!\n\n\nMeet at our 
 Dero Fix-it station\, on Franklin Street.\n\n \n\n\n\n\nThis event is 
 generously sponsored by the Friends of the Mountain View Library.\n
LOCATION:Bike Fix-it Station (Outside Franklin St. Entrance)
ORGANIZER;CN="Kyle Hval":MAILTO:kyle.hval@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Health & Wellness
UID:LibCal-8800-15917714
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/15917714
END:VEVENT
