SUMMARY:Smart Start Babytime
DESCRIPTION:Smart Start Babytime is a special program for babies (0–2) 
 and their caregivers that blends stories\, songs\, and early play with 
 different information each week with a pediatric resident from Stanford 
 Medical School. Caregivers will gain practical tips\, build confidence\, 
 and have the opportunity to ask questions—all in a warm\, supportive 
 environment designed for your baby’s earliest learning.\n
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Alex Pantazes":MAILTO:alexandra.pantazes@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Learn & Explore, Parenting, Storytime
