BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20270108T233000Z
DTEND:20270109T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20270108T000000Z
SUMMARY:Pages and Paws Reading Buddy
DESCRIPTION:Therapy reading dogs provide a comforting presence for children 
 as they navigate the exciting realm of books.\n\nThis initiative aims to 
 build confidence\, enhance literacy skills and instill a lifelong love for 
 reading.\n\nTherapy dogs plan to visit on the first Friday of each month\, 
 but review our calendar to confirm dates. Limited registration is 
 intentional to allow readers rewarding one-on-one reading time with a 
 therapy dog.\n\nThis month\, up to three threapy dogs will be visiting. 
 More details on your confirmed time-slot\, and instruction to follow once 
 registered.\n\nAges 8-12.
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Richard Hansen":MAILTO:richard.hansen@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Read
UID:LibCal-8800-16357823
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/16357823
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20270114T023000Z
DTEND:20270114T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20270113T000000Z
SUMMARY:Ukulele Jam Sing and Play Along
DESCRIPTION:Registration is recommended. Seating is limited. Walk-ins are 
 also welcome. \n\nWould you like to learn some fun songs on the ukulele? 
 Beginners and ukulele enthusiasts are welcome to join us to sing and play 
 together. Ukulele instructor Chuck Monahan will teach participants how to 
 play basic chords on the ukulele and lead the group in an informal 
 performance of popular songs from the last 50 years. Bring your own uke\, 
 or use one of ours. \n\nAges 12 and up only.\n\n \n\n\n\nThis event is 
 generously sponsored by the Friends of the Mountain View Library.\n
LOCATION:1st Floor Program Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Ashley Lang":MAILTO:ashley.lang@mountainview.gov
CATEGORIES:Just For Fun (Adult)
UID:LibCal-8800-17028031
URL:https://mountainview.libcal.com/event/17028031
END:VEVENT
